Here is a super sweet video from our beloved Matilda (aka @crazyheadcomics), the independent artist who we collaborated with this month for our Mental Health Awareness campaign, including the Feelings Chart Magnet we've been including FREE with all orders of $60+ 💕

🎉  Tomorrow is Matilda's birthday! Happy Birthday from our Self-Care community, @crazyheadcomics! 🎂 Thank you for all the love and talent you share with us 🥰

🙊 To celebrate, we sent her a package with all of her new designs, and it was delightful to be invited to view her unboxing. It is always an honor to experience the joy of an artist holding their designs in their hands for the first time.

We hope you love this video as much as we did!! 😊

Have you been wanting to prioritize your mental health, but haven’t been able to? 🧠 

Well this is your sign! ✨

💚 This month, we have teamed up with @betterhelp in giving away FREE therapy (1 month of it) in every purchase from our BetterHelp x @selfcareisforeveryone collection, as illustrated by @almudena.rocca ! 💗

🙏 Therapy can provide you with a safe space to be heard and tell your story and we wanted to give you & the rest of this beautiful community an opportunity to try therapy for free and without commitment!

💕 Know someone who can benefit from a month of free therapy? Pick up an item from this limited collection for them — not only are you gifting them with a gentle reminder on a garment, but you’ll also be gifting them with the potentially life-altering gift of trying and accessing therapy. 

👇 Tag someone in your life that may appreciate receiving a FREE month of therapy!

🧠 Mental Health Check In:
✨ How are you feeling about the month ahead? 

👇 Comment an emoji below!! 

🙂 hopeful 
🥳 excited
😇 grateful
😖 anxious
🥸 not ready
😞 overwhelmed

Responding to someone else in the comments with some love and kindness is encouraged 💗

#community

💕✨😊🙏

♥️ If you need support in a challenging time:

What you are experiencing can really impact your mental health and ability to focus. We wanted to include some resources of where you can reach out for support if it ever feels quite challenging. 🙏

All US residents can Text HOME to 741741 Crisis Text Line is available 24/7 to connect you with a trained crisis counselor ready to help you through any situation you’re finding challenging. This can range from school stress to coronavirus anxiety, depression to suicidal thoughts, and everything in between. A safe and confidential platform, Crisis Text Line can help you through your most difficult moments.

To find more resources (including inside or outside of the USA) check out our Mental Health Resources on our website. ♥️🙏 It’s okay to ask for help, you are not alone!!

Sending you all so much love ♥️🌈

node.accessibility_caption: Kindness is cool

node.text:
5️⃣ Kind Things To Do This Weekend 🦋

1️⃣ Smile at yourself in a mirror. Be kind to yourself 🙂

2️⃣ Reach out to a friend you haven’t connected with in a while. Share some words of encouragement and kindness with them. ♥️

3️⃣ Smile at a stranger or give them a compliment, you never know what someone is going through. 💕

4️⃣ Sign up to volunteer somewhere this week, your time can really make an impact in your local community. 📞

5️⃣ Write a thank you letter to someone who has really impacted your life. Share the letter with them if you choose. 📝

( 📸 “Kindness is Cool” on an Ivory Long Sleeve)

node.text:
Simone Biles has shown us why it’s so important for the world to be reminded of the very real existence and importance of mental health. 🧠

😞 It’s been clear how much stigma there still is among the general public around putting your own mental health needs above anything else.

Let’s make one message very clear: MENTAL HEALTH IS PHYSICAL HEALTH. 🧠💪

🙏 Thank you to everyone in our community for being mental health advocates in the world and wearing these messages for others to see. Together, we will end the stigma surrounding mental health and true self-care. You don't have to have a huge platform to make a difference, your voice matters 📣

🤸🏿‍♀️Simone was brave enough to prioritize her mental health on the biggest stage imaginable and it’s created a wave of much needed dialogue around these topics. 🌊

In the brave AND wise words of Simone… “Put your mental health first.” The louder we get about this, collectively, the more we will ALL get to enjoy a healthier, more supportive & more stigma-free future. Sending you and the rest of this community so much love 💕🍄

( 🎨 on sweatshirt by @blessthemessy and @kustartt )

Thank you @simonebiles for being a mental health advocate and role model and reminding us all that it’s okay to prioritize your mental health over work and professional achievements — even the Olympics. 

“I say put mental health first, because if you don’t then you’re not going to enjoy your sport and you’re not going to succeed as much as you want to. So it’s okay to sometimes even sit out of the big competition to focus on yourself because it shows how strong of a competitor and person that you really are, rather than just battling through it.” - @simonebiles

node.accessibility_caption: Self-care day. Self-care is for everyone.

node.text:
We usually unplug on Saturdays... but NOT today; Today is International Self-Care Day!! 🎉🎉🎉

We call ourselves Self-Care Is For Everyone because we believe everyone can benefit from practicing self-care. 💕

✨ We envision a future where everyone is aware of their inherent self-worth, conversations around mental health are normalized, and individuals know that they can reach out for help when needed.
 
🐛 Self-care is a practice of showing up for yourself and listening to what you’re needing so that you can continue showing up each and every day. Self-care is not always easy and sometimes self-care can be uncomfortable. 

Through self-care, we learn to develop a healing-centered relationship to our day-to-day emotional and mental health. 🌼

♥️ We hope that our garments, posters, and accessories serve as reminders throughout your day to check in with yourself and consider practicing an act of self-care in your day.

We love serving this community and we cannot wait for you to see all of the work we’ve been putting in these past few months. Thank you for showing up and doing the work alongside of us 🦋

💕 “Self-care keeps me alive and reminds me of my own strength.” 

🔋“Self-care helps me fill up my physical and mental battery”

🌻 “It validates that I am a valuable and worthy person” 

Self-care is not always easy, but it definitely matters. That is why we are so eager to celebrate and honor Self-Care Day!! 🐛✨
